"Dreams are really important to me. I think the world you experience when you’re dreaming is physically real, in some way. I don’t understand it at all, but I’ve had enough intense experiences to justify that belief. For me, it’s a sort of parallel reality to our normal, waking consciousness – one where time doesn’t exist and dead relatives can hang out with you. Whenever I’m making art or music, I feel like I’m trying to reach over into that place and bring some of it back into this one."

The Swiss mad beat scientist PulpFusion, starts out as a guitar player in a few local bands over 20 years ago. But the love for producing and mixing groove ‘n funk rooted music, make him decide to take the turntable path. Looking for a personal style, he writes, plays and produces his own music that finds it’s way to the audience during intensive gigs and concerts all over Switzerland.
The sound of PulFusion gets the attention from other artists, asking him to produce and (re)mix their songs. This resolves in various international collaborations.
In 2007 he decides to come up with the record-label ‘Pig Balls Records’, originally intended to release his own mix of groove, trip-hop, soul, funk ‘n jazz beats. But with several number 1 charts at Junodownload in no time, other artists quickly find their way to the Pig Balls Label.
And yet, there’s still a hunger for more… DJ PulpFusion launches a second label named ‘Booty Pirates’ to release a few heavy weight remixes and mash-ups. Every single release makes it to the number 1 position in the charts of Junodownload and other internet sites.
 
Anno 2011, PulpFusion is well known in the international Funk and Breaks scene as a producer, but the heart still belongs to the stage! Experiencing DJ PulpFusion live takes the audience on a journey to good old fashioned soul, funk and all related styles of the vinyl era combined with the forces of today’s killer beats.
Let the grooves Pump!

Nicolas Canot is a sound/digital artist, improviser, guitar player and teacher based in Reims, France.

His work is focused for several years on electronic/electroacoustic music and sound creations, often relative to real or fictional acoustic spaces (binaural works, headphones live performances, computer controlled rotating speakers, multi-channels sound installations etc). His sound creations/installations were performed/showed in France, England, Romania, Portugal, Canada, Poland.

He performs as a solo artist and regularly collaborates with visual or sound artists as well as jazz instrumentalists.

He’s an associated artist, curator, publisher, translator for 23.03 [art contemporain collective : http://www.2303.fr/] as well as former artist of Tacomma [improvised music collective].

He also teaches sound art theory, history & practices, conducting workshops in High Schools and Universities using softwares such as Max/MSP/Jitter, Pure Data, Ableton Live, Arduino etc.

Appropriating their name from the first culture of the old world to explore the new, Phoenecia, aka Josh Kay & Romulo Del Castillo, was inaugurated in Miami in 1997. The pair had previously recorded under the Soul Oddity moniker, releasing an album & a series of 12-inch singles for the US major label Astralwerks. In late 1996 they founded Schematic Music Company, a record label which would go on to carve a distinct niche in the landscape of modern music by debuting releases from some of the most notable & influential electronic musicians of the twentieth century. In 2001 they released a full-length album entitled Brownout, which in the words of the late Tim Haslett was "Phoenecia's magnum opus, the place where the ideas found in the preceding records are allowed to come to full fruition... the compositions are cinematic, in the respect that the tracks are heavily influenced by the sound design of film, as opposed to the score". This album marked a decisive break from Phoenecia's rhythmic past & set the trajectory for the sound they would continue to develop over the next decade in their most recent albums Echelon Mall & Demissions.

fascinated by music since his earliest days, James first stumbled upon the raw sonic energy of early house, techno, early rave and other experimental sounds coming out of Chicago, Detroit and elsewhere in the mid 90's..

20+ years since acquiring his own 1200's and beginning his journey, he remains dedicated to the art of digging as well as sculpting and defining his own sound built one show at a time. over several hundred events in Chicago and later in Detroit, Miami, San Francisco, Melbourne, London, Juarez, Sofia, Tokyo and elsewhere, he has opened for major international touring artists including Chris Liebing, Juan Atkins, Richie Hawtin, Derrick Carter, Diz, Sandra Collins, James Murphy (LCD Soundsystem), John Digweed, Diplo, Tiesto, Satoshi Tomiie, Richard Fearless (Death In Vegas), Steve Lawler, Lee Foss, Nathan Coles, Way Out West and many more..

Based in Los Angeles since 2013, James always enjoys the chance to share his deep love for the Midwest and his dedication to it's rich musical heritage and roots. This can be clearly heard and more importantly felt in his dynamic vinyl-based DJ sets as well as live performance. His passion for the music and modern DIY production methods have also informed his ongoing studio efforts including his own analogue-style productions, remixes and collaborations.

Grant Aaron, founder of the long-running podcast series Mysteries of the Deep, has spent decades immersing himself in electronic music. His influences are far-reaching, and his identity resists categorization: he is both an ambient and techno DJ, and is a core member in the band Birds of Prey. As its name implies, Mysteries of the Deep is concerned with exploration of unknown realms, and its focus—in addition to showcasing a dynamic spectrum of electronic music from foremost artists in the field—is to thoughtfully engage its audience. Based in New York and conceptualized in 2011, Mysteries—as fans lovingly call it—began as a podcast series that, now in its tenth year, has hosted mixes and original works by Patrick Russell, Tobias, Tropic Of Cancer, Aleksi Perälä, Neel, ASC, Antenes, DJ Pete (Substance), Chris SSG, and many others. 

The project has since evolved, expanding into a curated event series and in recent years, a burgeoning record label. Since 2018, Mysteries released several albums, EPs, and an expansive compilation series. Grant has produced Mysteries events in Brooklyn, Tokyo, Seoul, and Taipei, where he has performed extended DJ sets, or played live with Birds. 

As a DJ, Grant invokes and constructs narrative shapes from the nebulous ether of ambient and experimental music. He references kosmische tradition, synthesizer elegance from Detroit and the U.K., cold drone moods, and leftfield futurism from Asia and the Americas. He's performed at marquee venues throughout North America, Europe, and Asia, is a resident at the world-renowned Detroit party No Way Back, and has released mixes for Resident Advisor, Smoke Machine from Taipei, Sure Thing from New York, Oslated from Seoul,  Beyond/Below from Chicago, and Silent Season from Vancouver. 

Website: mysteriesofthedeep.net/grant-aaron
Booking inquiries: info@mysteriesofthedeep.net

The history of supergroover: Supergroover started in 2002 with some local underground parties but soon expanded to other sides of the world. So far Europe has been infected (Belgium, Netherlands, Germany & Sweden) and the Americas as well (Canada, USA, Mexico, Guatemala & Bolivia). Small parties and larger festivals as well have been supergrooved (Antaris, Fullmoon & Fusion Festival for example). The choice of music depends of the time of day, indoor or outdoor, the wishes of the crowd and the rest of the line up. His sets are dynamic and not preplanned. They go from relaxed chillout with humour through funky technoish progressive psytrance with a friendly touch to active progressive psytrance dancefloor madness, but the funky groovy progressive stuff mostly. All material he uses is cd quality. For several reasons. First off all he simply wants to provide the audience with the best quality possible. Seeing many dj’s nowadays playing mp3’s, Supergroover holds the view that the psytrance scene must be fed and kept healthy by spending some bucks for your music.
For a few years Supergroover has been producing progressive psytrance. He has been making up a nice mix of atmospheric sounds with an active underlayer of kick & bass topped with acid influenced sounds and melodies. His music fits nicely between progressive and fullon. Words can only say so much..

Dan Bain says that DJs just play other people’s music. His humility, however, cloaks the fact that his DJ sets sound like his own harmonious song. Vocals that ripple, keys that drip, and buoyant percussion are the standard to this Detroit native.
Bain cannot be whittled down to a genre. Having traversed the dunes of house and techno, to the crest of indie and trip-hop, he maintains a unique presence. His sense of victory comes by reach- ing even one person in the audience, although the majority hold on for the duration of the set. His sonic language comforts the dancer who is heartbroken, gyrates the weekend warrior, enlightens the lost, and flirts with the rest, even leaving his own heart on the dance floor.
With an ever-expanding music collection that includes his favorite 12"s, LPs and 45s, Dan’s depth of knowledge hints at an insatiable quest of the universal language. On any given night, whether his message is through hip-hop, heartfelt house, or the quickened pace of techno, there is always a gentle let-down, but never a conclusion. You’ll have to return for the next chapter in the story.

Omid Mahramzadeh, also known as PrOmid, is an international music producer, composer, DJ, remixer, vocalist, and sound engineer, who has developed a remarkable innovation in chill-out and house genres. His music is a composition of native musical instruments with a western musical atmosphere, this unique approach to merging traditional native eastern instruments with the electronic western atmosphere has won him critical acclaim around the globe.  His prolific talent has seen him producing music in progressive house, trance, and techno, the tracks he has produced for the Buddha Bar series are amongst the most downloaded chill-out albums of all time. His knowledge and technical expertise in merging indigenous traditional musicianship with contemporary electronic compositions are what makes PrOmids music truly exceptional and unique. PrOmids' attentive approach makes for his outstanding genre-defining music, by bringing ancient sounds into a modern context he is pushing the boundaries of eastern electronic music. PrOmid is not only a master of his craft, his pushing music has the power to transfix and transport the listener into the future whilst also creating a zone of mystery by combining the futurist soundscapes with the instrumentation of an ancient civilization, his outstanding musical innovation mesmerizes anyone who listens to his music

The group named TRYB [tribe] was formed on the spring of 2002 by the collaboration Kürt Filipe(79') [rhythm] ,Tom-x Gaviali(73') [melodies] and R2K(79') [lyrics and concepts] .

Before 2000 Kürt Filipe and R2K have already worked on collaborated projects in another formation. Their style was a mix techno with abstract melodies.

When Tom-x Gaviali joined them ,it was only after months of experimenting that they settled within the genre of Trance. As the years passed ,the members of the group became obsessed by the genre .The true goal of their work is to unfold real emotions in their ,and make the style more popular in the region .

The album called "HERE AND NOW" ,was made within the melodical world of trance music.Besides the 12 tracks also ,an unplugged version of a song can be found ,so the composers could show they also have experience in other musical fields.

Tom-x Gaviali

His interest in music goes back to the eighties ,where he was amazed by the sounds and music made by synthesizer .He is still influenced today by analogue synthesizer sounds and the techno pop era .
Although group's instrumentation is slightly hard ,its still the emotions and melodies that play the main role within his music.

R2K

His inspiration for abstract melodies come from software's and cyber culture. All the lyrics are made by him. Besides lyrics, he has enriched the group with his musical concepts and ideas.

Kürt Filipe

He started as a techno DJ - this is how his interest in music creation has started. He is responsible for the arrangements and the rhythms within the songs. He is the engine of the team.

Music producer and multi-instrumentalist

Creativity and performance have been a part of my life from an early age. Music and Sound has been a major form of expression for me in the last few years.

I also have a passion for creative writing, photography, theatre and dance and I hope to fuse my musical knowledge with these creative interests in the future.

The dissection of compound sounds, to create simple textures and perceived environments and the process of creating complex architectural structures within music gives me creative satisfaction.

I have explored different genres as a musician, my role in the band "Khadki Junction Blues" as the bass player and producer helped me work with musicians playing blues, rock, jazz, Indian classical and funk. I have recorded over two albums and worked on film scores with the band.

A brief stint with a 'Live Sound' company and my Diploma in Audio Engineering, helped me explore the challenges faced by a live sound engineer working on conferences for multi national companies and Jazz and Bollywood concerts.

My interest in experimentation and technology brought me to 'The Queensland University of Technology' to pursue a Bachelor's Degree in Sound Design.

Combining Live instruments, samples, Indian elements and computer generated sounds are a major part of my 'Experimental Fusion' compositions.

I force myself not to be influenced by others, I believe in originality and innovation however human nature forces me to borrow ideas from artistic works I have experienced.

I am inspired by the merciless, mechanical functioning of Indian cities, the loopholes, chaos and complexities of social and political systems, nature, animals, our perishing planet and the concept of extra-terrestrials.

I believe mathematics, physics and architecture which I find intriguing yet incomprehensible, inspire me at an unconscious level.

Brian Transeau, Telefon TelAviv, Prefuse 73, Jack Johnson, Michael Jackson, Nitin Sawhney, Richard Branson, Steve Mc Curry and Johnny Depp are humans who inspire me artistically.

My future interests include collaborating with other musicians, combining my creative interests and creating complex soundscapes for films and abstract visualisations.

I plan to incorporate programming in my compositions and I plan to devote time towards the development of new musical instruments and creative editing techniques in the near future.

Conan Liquid doesn’t buy into sub genres; only good music. With a faultless technical ability honed from years of studying his craft – this man wrote a thesis on the technology of mix downs- and his athenaeum sized catalogue of tunes a Conan Liquid set is a grooving journey and rhythmic education (of tracks you didn’t even know you loved) from start to finish. 
Conan does have big bragging rights, but you won’t hear him name-dropping. His passion is firmly placed in making music and spinning tracks. 
His turntable journey started out by playing hip hop and disco records in 1983 but in 1987 he heard the classic 80’s House gem by Ten City, “That’s the way love is”. 
Conan was signed to Strictly Rhythm at 26 after a coming of age trip to NYC with the formidable Gladys Pizarro; returning to the UK armed with a bucket full of jaw dropping stories and crate picked hardware from the East Village. Conan released ‘Sunny’s Theme”, a Bucketheads disco styled opus and this track led him onto peer-championed classics ‘One time for your mind’ and “Bring it back”. 
With over 400 releases to his name and a main room staple on the international Clubbing circuit, taking in almost every continent and major clubbing brand, including an appearance on Top of The Pops for his top 40 track ‘Monster’ (yes seriously), Conan has captivated dance floors with both his solo and Liquid People projects. 
Championed by the best in the business (we said we wouldn’t name drop but seriously take a look at this list): Masters at work, Todd Terry, Pete Tong, DJ Spen, Dave Lee, Frankie Knuckles, Tony Humphries, Roger S, his extremely impressive discography features on many major labels including MN2s, Tropical Disco, Defected Records, Strictly Rhythm, Sony, Z records, Africanism, Launch, Big Love and Catch 22 and productions for artists including Ashanti, Lighthouse Family, Talking Heads, Todd Terry, Radiohead, Blondie, Imogen Heap and All Saints. 
Conan now resides in Dubai where he runs the boutique label Crates Motel Records.
Due to his incredible technical ability, production and beat programming skills you can expect a faultless set of good quality music, with live re-edits, and live remixing on the fly. Few DJs can say they have remained at the top of a scene for over 30 years, yet this man can.
Genres: Deep House, Funk, Jazz, Disco, Lounge.

Overload Promotion was created in 2006 and has comprised an idea of advancement of drum’n’bass music in cultural layers of the population of Moscow. The promo-group was finally based after one
crazy party which was a continuation of the performance of a famous rapper Smoki Mo. After that the basic structure of Overload Crew was defined: april2die (dj duke nukem), Dr. Che, s3t selectah and Solid.

At the beginning the promo residents and the invited visitors pushed “heavier in weights” sound, being based on such styles as drum’n’bass, tech-step, dark-step and hard-step. Further the musical component of a command has accepted more or less humane, mainstream sounding. Oldskool jump up and fervent clownstep have replaced brutal forcemeat of darkside and and have started to prevail on the dancefloors of Overload parties.

In connection with these changes the company has organised the Free-parties set in the centre of Moscow under the name “All About Drum’n’Bass” which have strongly affected further promo-group development. The key moment was the performance in Jest’ club which collected lots of people and had original, powerful energy. On one of such parties the participant of the first Ukrainian ragga-jungle command, “the daddy” of Ukrainian ragga-jungle Taras Polischuk aka Stepkillah performed in Moscow for the first time .

After the above described event Overload Promotion and Ukrainian ragga-jungle lovers co-operate and keep in contact. At present, the company, as they say, has returned to roots and gives the majority of time to jungle and ragga-jungle music. For today it is possible to consider Overload Crew as undeground collective as the idea of all promotion at present is the maintenance and advancement of Russian jungle music and cultures at level of people who really understand and appreciate it as a modern art integral part. Now members of Overload are engaged in producing their own music and preparing something new for you.

I Wannabe is one of the most relevant drum’n’bass producers from Kyiv. His fascination with electronic music coincided with the “golden ten” of the 90s. It was then that Andrey heard the Space "Magic Fly" plate, which was the beginning of a journey into the world of beats and synthesizers. The EZ Rollerz “Meatball” record became the point of no return in his musical consciousness. Since 2000, the drum’n’bass style has become the guiding star of Andrey’s creative explorations.

Sorting out different sequencers and genres, Andrew honed his own style. So, starting in 2007, I Wannabe's tracks have been released on such labels as Formation, 22:22, Disturbed, Cymbalism, Rubik, Inception:Audio, Machinist Music, Kos.Mos.Music and get essential support from London Elektricity, Bailey, B.Traits, RSD, Dodge & Fuski, Chris Inperspective, Cutworx, Electrosoul System, Gvozd, Need For Mirrors, DJ Trax and Noisia.

I Wannabe gained wide popularity in Ukraine thanks to remixes for local artists - Kazka, Zapaska, Pluton & Skyer, Mauoq, Atomic Simao, Freel, Katya Chilly and alyona alyona. In 2018, Andrey launched his own label Deviant Drums, which releases drum'n’bass exclusively on vinyl. The circulation of the debut release of the I Wannabe “Dreams” EP with remixes from Commix and Total Science was sold out in a month, raising a stir in the world’s drum’n’bass community.

Nowadays, I Wannabe is focused on production for both his own label as well as well-known worldwide ones. He actively performs in Ukraine and is available for booking around the world.

Ant J Steep has been a central figure in the Australian underground dance music scene since the late 90's. As a DJ he has been a pioneer in developing the vibrant underground house scene that is now flourishing in his hometown of Melbourne through some important residencies at the cities’ most influential clubs where he would hold his own against some of the world’s most respected DJs.

Beginning his career in the late 90’s spinning a mixture of funk, hip-hop, drum n’ bass, techno and house, Ant developed the ability to cross a variety of styles or hone in on one hypnotic vibe. By the early 2000’s Ant began pushing the underground house sounds that were emerging in Europe and the American West Coast and started putting on his own events, club nights and touring Dj’s from all over the world. He held residencies at some of Melbourne and Sydney's most iconic venues and parties, such as Lounge, Spice, Reckless Republic and Subsonic, but it was his five-year residency at the seminal Honkytonks that really put him on the international map and bookings began flowing in for South America, Europe, and the USA.

As a producer Ant has had his fair share of success. His Little Beasties project found its way into record bags the world over and was even hailed by BBC’s Pete Tong as one of his essential tunes. He has released records on London’s Music For Freaks, Sheffield’s Odori, France’s Tome Bone, Germany’s Morris Audio and Australia’s Future Classic, LightSpeed and Freak Show Disco to name a few. His current psychedelic pop project Fang Jnr is already gaining critical praise for the 2015 album "Dimensioneer's"

Ant is now residing in Los Angeles

'English Folk meets Americana. Beautiful stuff' - BBC Introducing

Coley Garratts songs are steeped in the rich musical traditions of his home, best exemplified by the early Folk superstars of Bert Jansch, John Martyn, Nick Drake and Richard Thompson to name just a few.  At the same time he draws much inspiration from the great Americana troubadours and balladeers such as Bob Dylan, Neil Young, Ryan Adams and The Band.

He constantly wanders between these two vast musical landscapes mining for songs. Any gems he is lucky enough to find get washed and cut through his unique lyrical perspective which have been inspired by a deep love of Poetry, Philosophy and Mysticism (Pope, Shakespeare, Ted Hughes, Schopenhauer, Huxley and the Tao Te Ching to name just a handful) 

Over the years he has written hundreds of songs in a constant labour of love to perfect his craft and is currently in the process of recording and cataloguing as many of them as possible.
  
His self-titled debut EP released in May 2019 is a 5 song collection of some previous recordings as an Introduction. 

New videos are also available on YouTube.

Having over 30 releases out there on many different labels, soundaddict Rogier Habraken a.k.a. Mindmapper lost his status as "new-comer" long ago. Thanks to support of many keyfigures within the scene, he has laid down a solid foundation for the future. Backed up by many gigs, residencies and appearances on events, radioshows and festivals in both the Netherlands and abroad. Next to that he's co-owner of Break-Fast Audio, sound designer and mix engineer for Dutch broadcasting and has a curating duty for the online music discovery service 22tracks.com.

Coming from a background of working with bands, playing piano, double bass and electric guitar for many years and building his own studio, Mindmapper has got all the musical skills a producer might want. What started out as recording and arranging songs played by his band, evolved in a serious affection for cutting, sampling and composing electronic music. Combined with his education as an Audio Designer, Mindmapper is a musical mastermind whose style expands way beyond just Drum & Bass. 

It's hard to describe his broad spectrum of productions in few words but one can find all sort of influences ranging from techno to rock and dub to classical. His tunes and collabarations tend to explore the "boundaries" of the genre and have been spotted, not surprisingly, by a broad audience. Support comes from Loxy, Doc Scott, Hazard, Hype, Octane & DLR, D-Kay, Bailey, Fabio, Consequence, Gremlinz, June Miller amongst many others. With material forthcoming on Samurai Music, Dispatch, Eternia Music, Soundium X, Creative Wax and CX, 2013 looks bright.

we are MCC from Sweden. We play Magical Rock Music.

Or, as we sometimes call it: “Radio-edited movie themes, for daily life and death”.

Our music reminds of Vangelis meeting Tom Petty, trying to reach U2, willing to be Joy Division, feeling like ABBA, longing to be Brian Eno, remembering Jean Michel Jarre, looking at Metallica, sleeping with Mike Oldfield, dancing to Koto, hunting the Beatles, killing Morricone in a duel, snorting to Moroder etc etc.

London based Clear The Dance Floor have opened up for the Scratch Perverts, Jungle Drummer & Dj FU, Fabio, Ray Keith, Dj EZ and the Artful Dodger as a live act. Being able to open up for such a diverse range of acts whilst still adding a very personal touch is why they continue to be a favourite with fans and promoters alike.

When not opening up for bigger acts, they are clearing saturated commercial dance floors up and down the country on a regular basis with underground genre crossing sets.

Drawing influences from hip hop, house, breaks, rock, drum & bass, reggae, ambient... their productions fully utilise this eclectic melting pot. As they are aware that no one is paying for music these days, you can download their tracks for free on this page. Expect everything from underground house to sub banging hip hop to chill out, nothing is off limits.

You can find promotional mixes up for grabs here, giving you a little taster of what to expect live.
